        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <h4 class="font-semibold">Rationale</h4>
  <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
    <li>
      <strong>MSM as a separate call:</strong> Providing a dedicated Multi-Scalar Multiplication (MSM) precompile is more gas-efficient than performing many individual multiplication and addition calls. It saves on both computational cost (by using algorithms like Pippenger's) and the overhead of multiple <code>CALL</code> opcodes.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>No dedicated MUL call:</strong> A separate multiplication (MUL) precompile is unnecessary because a single multiplication is just an MSM with one pair (<code>k=1</code>). The MSM precompile handles this case efficiently.
    </li>
  </ul>
